Quote: Many of the details regarding the sayings and doings of the islanders may be [iv] accounted as being of too simple a nature for record; ... <i>Ibid.</i> 1/76 I ... proceeded to the village with the inhabitants ... uttering, with deafening shouts, `Airemai [e-acute]! airemai [e-acute]!' - welcome! welcome! ... accompanied by a ... waving of mats, and other expressions of applause, which are so liberally bestowed by these islanders, on those whom they may choose to honour.
